        "id": 1206284
      },
      "writtenOn": "2020-07-15T21:19:29Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "hwfeature is fine to start ... main point is ... the scope of the dataset available for filtering is larger\n\ne.g. if you wanted to restrict to a 2nd sourced component (wifi chip, etc...) ... this is beyond the scope of hwfeatures",
      "parentUuid": "3e81da68_6d4602bb",
      "revId": "1e7db3b2782b354097cb2b589a3f3f72507c14a5",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "aef7daf9_99c8ac9d",
        "filename": "src/chromiumos/tast/bundle/args.go",
        "patchSetId": 6
      },
      "lineNbr": 127,
      "author": {
        "id": 1166720
      },
      "writtenOn": "2020-07-16T05:41:58Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "What do you mean by \"a 2nd sourced component\"? Is it same as \"something infra scheduler don\u0027t do\"?\n\nI think it is OK when Tast requires more filtering than done in the infra scheduler. In such case we will need to add more data inside Tast code here by introducing another data struct, in order to store information polled from DUT by Tast. That is #2 scenario, and will be enclosed inside the Tast codebase.\n\nOur intention is that hardwareFeature should cover what it covers only.\nWhen the shceduler in the infra introduce a new hardware feature for filtering, it will be added to the config proto. Then that field becomes also available in the code here, so that we can implement the counterpart in Tast more smoothly.",
      "parentUuid": "d32e10af_5f3aba84",
      "revId": "1e7db3b2782b354097cb2b589a3f3f72507c14a5",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "6ec8d807_4fa8cc65",
        "filename": "src/chromiumos/tast/bundle/args.go",
        "patchSetId": 6
      },
      "lineNbr": 127,
      "author": {
        "id": 1206284
      },
      "writtenOn": "2020-07-16T13:12:23Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "2nd sources means during manufacturing, different components can be used (for cost/availability reasons) as long as they are considered feature identical\n\ne.g. (these are 2nd sourceable components that are def\u0027d in autotest)\nhttps://cs.corp.google.com/chromeos_public/src/third_party/autotest/files/client/common_lib/cros/network/interface.py?q\u003dintel+wifi+f:autotest\u0026g\u003d0\u0026l\u003d27\n\nthis dataset will not come from hardwarefeature (cause that just focuses on the specs/features) and doesn\u0027t understand the concept of 2nd sourcing\n\ni\u0027m fine starting with hwfeatures, but think we should include the full dataset domain eventually to support these types of cases",
      "parentUuid": "aef7daf9_99c8ac9d",
      "revId": "1e7db3b2782b354097cb2b589a3f3f72507c14a5",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
